an unpolarized deuteron beam
The isotopically enriched target (96.3%) was prepared
by vacuum  evaporation on a 4 mu-g/cm2 thick carbon
backing.
Reaction products were
momentum-separated by the  Q3D spectrograph and
detected in a 399mm long position sensitive cathode
strip  detector. This detector was a combination of a
proportional chamber with a scintillator in which the
particles were stopped and yielded an energy-rest
signal.

x4freetext: The polarized beam from a Lamb-shift
source was accelerated to 18 MeV with a vector
polarization of the beam of about 60%.
The target was a foil of natural W
The beam intensity was integrated in a Faraday cup
Relative intensities for all angles  were converted to
the absolute scale (microbarn/sr.) by means of the
separate   measurements performed at Theta=40 degr.
and 18 MeV on the enriched sample  of 186W (99.8%).
The outgoing protons were recorded
on a 1.8 m long focal plane detector. It consisted of
an array of single-wire proportional chambers followed
by a plastic scintillator for particle identification
